Fig. 2: Deviations from random coil 13Cα and 13Cβ chemical shifts in the protein nsp3(1066–1181) plotted versus the amino acid sequence. The ΔδCα and ΔδCβ values were determined with the program package ATNOS/CANDID (Herrmann et al. 2002a, b) by subtracting the random coil 13Cα and 13Cβ shifts from the experimentally determined chemical shifts. The Δδi value for residue i represents a three-point average value over the three consecutive residues i − 1, i and i + 1, calculated as follows: 
